reviews.text:
We went there for lunch and ordered the Salmon Risotto, and the Fish of the Day (which was halibut). The Risotto was creamy and delicious. The fish was fresh, and nicely grilled. Both dishes were quite good. 

Service wise, the waitresses were polite. Both once the restaurant got crowded, they were overwhelmed. I called for the bill and it took them over 15 mins to bring it. 

Being right by the sea, the location is great. Definitely a place to come for drinks with a couple of friends.

Was asked if there was something wrong with my fish (had fish & chips) since I didn't each much of it. I said yeah, it was really salty. (I'm a former chef and my salt tolerance is actually pretty high - and I couldn't eat this). 

The waitress just nodded and walked away.

The bill came. No discount. No apology. Nothing. 

Expecting the customer to pay the full amount for a dish they couldn't eat? These guys have obviously not received proper training.
The food is definitely overpriced and tastes bad.
Food are ok, not bad.  It is a place for relaxing and meeting with friends.
Very good seafood. The grilled lobster is excellent.
